 application rejected if your FICO score is a few points away from optimal.\n\n$PGY is a second look service that uses over 1,600 variables (transactional data, cash flow behavior, and real-time macro signals) to evaluate the risk of your application.\n\n$PGY has processed over $3,6 trillion in loan applications since inception.\n\nThat\u2019s how much data $PGY AI is being trained on. The more data $PGY processes, the better its AI gets.\n\nBut its business model goes beyond big commercial banks like JP Morgan.\n\n$PGY connects the banks with institutional investors. It doesn\u2019t originate loans, the banks do.\n\nThe moment that happens, $PGY takes them off the bank\u2019s balance sheet, bundles multiple loans together, and sells them to institutional investors.\n\nIt\u2019s a triple win:\n\n1/ The bank reduces its risk because it no longer holds the loan\n\n2/ $PGY takes a cut for bundling and servicing the loans\n\n3/ The institutional investors buy a low-risk asset to collect interest on it\n\nDespite the current strain in the lending market, $PGY\u2019s business has never done better.\n\nIn 2026 so far, $PGY has secured $1,4 billion in funding from 26North and Sound Point Capital Management and closed $1,65 billion in transactions.\n\nThe latest transaction was rated AAA by Fitch Ratings.\n\nLong $PGY.", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 2, "replyCount": 8, "likeCount": 26, "quoteCount": 0, "viewCount": 1388, "createdAt": "Wed Apr 29 03:05:00 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 1, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2049324040754442332", "displayTextRange": [0, 276], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "InvestorDenis", "url": "https://x.com/InvestorDenis", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/InvestorDenis", "id": "1605284864340545537", "name": "Investor Denis", "isVerified": false, "isBlueVerified": true, "verifiedType": null, "profilePicture": "https://pbs.twim